// Section 1: Object Scope and Historicity

= Object Scope and Historicity

== Documentation Status

This document captures the planned and in-progress state of a hand-engraving
project. The materials, tools, and methods described correspond to the
engraver's intended period-accurate practice; not every step has yet been
performed, and no photographs of completed components are included in this
version of the documentation. The engraver has prior tool-making experience
from making chasing tools and repoussé punches, and that experience underlies
the forging and heat-treatment procedures described in §§2.2 and 3.1. At
the time of this writing, one graver handle has been turned on the lathe
from cherry (_Prunus_ sp.). The graver blanks are 3/16-inch (4.8 mm) square
A2 tool steel bar stock, in transit at the time of writing. The workflow
will be light forging on the tang end to start a slight taper, then stock
removal (grinding, filing, sanding) to finish the cross-section, point
geometry, and tang profile, and finally burning the tangs into the cherry
handles. Additional handles and the hammered copper
plate are also still in progress and not yet documented photographically. Future revisions will incorporate photographic evidence
of the gravers, handles, plate, and any pulled paper impressions, together
with a dated process log. The paper should be read as period-appropriate
craft documentation that will be updated as work progresses.

